      "id": "14c39e9f_98844bb2",
      "file_path": "runtime-acm/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/acm/runtime/util/rest/CommonRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 39,
      "message": "Based on what this class does, it should be named `CommonRestClient` instead of `Controller`. Controllers are for the server part of http communication",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2026-02-26 12:54:36.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "01391826_47615b26",
      "file_path": "runtime-acm/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/acm/runtime/util/rest/CommonRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 228,
      "message": "The more idiomatic way to do this would be to use constructor injection and register the `RestClient` as a `private final RestClient` on the class level.\n\nConstructor injection would also make sure that the trace context is maintained.\nThe way you are doing this here leads to disconnected traces for what should be one trace",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2026-02-26 12:54:36.000000000",
